Build Status Dialog Box

Requires: Base Development System

This dialog box appears when you are building a build specification.

When the build is complete, the name of the build specification and the path to the build specification files appear at the top of the dialog box.

  • Warning—Lists warnings that occur during the build specification. Expand the arrow to see the list of warnings.
  • Explore—Opens the destination directory where LabVIEW saves the build specification files. Clicking the Explore button also closes the Build Status dialog box.
  • Done—Closes the Build Status dialog box after the build is complete.
  • Cancel—Closes the Build Status dialog box before the build is complete and cancels the rest of the build.
